node.text: “If you can only be tall, because somebody’s on their knees, then you have a serious problem.” PLEASE start your Sunday watching this incredible clip with Toni Morrison. Charlie Rose (ugh) initially asks Morrison if she still encounters racism, despite her success. She turns the question around, explaining how racism is the only tool white supremacists have to undermine Black people’s success. It’s a timely and powerful clip with useful framing for understanding and confronting white supremacist terror in 2021.

node.title: Toni Morrison On Race And Racism

node.text:
Watch to the end to nod so hard your head falls off! Constitution expert Ben Sheehan (@bensheehan) is on the pod today to talk: ⁣
- How impeachment could happen way quicker than invoking the 25th amendment ⁣
-Options for barring Trump from holding office again ⁣
-Why there’s so much time between the election and inauguration?!? (It has to do with horses and buggies) ⁣
Find the Betches Sup podcast on Spotify, or on iTunes via betches.co/suppod (we’ll have a swipe up in Stories)⁣
⁣
You should 100% buy Ben’s book “OMG WTF Does The Constitution Actually Say.” We reference it on a weekly basis here at the Sup

node.title: How To Remove A President In 12 Days

node.text: We’ve received this question over and over, so here’s a clip from today’s podcast where we explain what to expect on Wednesday when Congress convenes to finalize the election result. We start with a simple explanation and then discuss what Republican senators are planning and how concerned we should be (it’s gonna be fine). *Why* are they doing this -- and why should that concern us just as much? Watch above, and subscribe at betches.co/suppod

node.text: Our penultimate episode of Save2020 is all about voter suppression. We dive into some of the most common questions surrounding voter suppression. How did it begin? What does it look like? And how tf are people still experiencing it in 2020? Your vote counts! We’re only one week away from the election, make sure your vote is counted.

node.text: In episode 7 of Save2020, we’re talking about gerrymandering. Wtf does it mean and how does it mess with who represents you in government? Why do politicians get to pick their voters instead of the other way around? We break down all of this and more and tell you how you can get involved in changing things.

node.title: Don't Know About Gerrymandering? It Knows A Lot About You

node.text: Where’s the line between celebrating femininity and falling into sexist tropes? Last month, Sup hosts sat down to discuss the question on all of our minds: is it sexist to stan Kamala Harris’s outfits? What do we signal to some women when we only celebrate others? Do we apply the same standard to women whose views we don’t agree with? It was a fascinating and cathartic conversation. Listen to the full episode at the link in bio/Stories betches.co/sexism

node.title: Is It Sexist To Stan Kamala Harris’s Outfits?

node.text:
Episode 6 of Save2020 is all about white supremacy and white privilege. We explain the difference between supremacy and privilege and trace the history back to the colonization of America. And in case it wasn’t already obvious enough, we give some 2020  examples of how both of those issues are at play today. ⁣
⁣
And as always, go to betches.co/save2020 for a DIRECT link to your board of elections. We are THREE WEEKS away from the election. Make sure you’re registered to vote and have your voting plan in place. ⁣
⁣
#politics #joebiden #donaldtrump #election2020 #2020election

node.title: Save2020 // Episode 6: White Supremacy Is Everywhere

node.text:
Episode 5 of Save2020 breaks down the problem with two party systems. We discuss the history of the two party system, what factors contributed to party alliances becoming so strong, and how the American “winner takes all” approach differs from political systems in other countries. ⁣
⁣
And head to betches.co/save2020 for a DIRECT link to your board of elections. We’re less than a month away from the election. Confirm your registration status and have your voting plan ready. (⭐️ @pandalise)

node.title: Save2020 // Episode 5: The Problems With A Two-Party System

node.text:
Tom Brady’s political past is sus, but the former guy definitely *hates* this. 

Trump is famously a huge Tom Brady fan, having enthusiastically defended Brady during the deflategate situation -- seeing himself in a fellow “winner” who he thought people were falsely rallying against. Brady said Trump called him often after games and the two went golfing together. Brady was spotted with a MAGA hat in his locker in 2015, but declined to say who he supported in 2016 and skipped a 2017 White House meeting with Trump. Trump was reportedly furious. 🎥 @cspan

node.text:
Any bed can be an anti-sex bed if you try hard enough. Amid some excited chatter that the cardboard beds created for Olympians and Paralympians may be designed to interfere with intimacy, turns out the beds can withstand up to 440 pounds and plenty of movement, as Irish gymnast Rhys McClenaghan demonstrated. The recylable frames are made by Japanese company Airweave, which says they’re stronger than steel. 

Olympic hookups pose threat of disease spread at every games, but concerns are obviously higher during a global pandemic. Athletes will still be provided condoms -- just at the end of the games. Hugs and handshakes are also discouraged.

node.text: Rupert Murdoch was vaccinated in December. Donald Trump in January. Yet both are benefiting from vaccine misinformation as millions tune into Fox News every night or donate to Trump. These people are literally making money by indulging dangerous delusions that are killing their viewers. Only 56% of American adults are fully vaccinated. More than 99 percent of people admitted to the hospital with COVID are unvaccinated. This is an emergency. 🚨
